SIMPLE: puisne
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Puisne
<hw>Puis"ne</hw> <pr>(p⟦umac⟧"n⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Puny</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Later in age, time, etc.;
subsequent.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧ A <xex>puisne</xex> date
to eternity.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Sir M. Hale.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Puny; petty; unskilled.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>Younger or inferior in rank;
junior; associate; <as>as, a chief justice and three <ex>puisne</ex>
justices of the Court of Common Pleas; the <ex>puisne</ex> barons of the
Court of Exchequer.</as></def> <rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Puisne</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Puisne
<hw>Puis"ne</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who is younger, or of inferior
rank; a junior; esp., a judge of inferior rank.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It were not a work for <qex>puisnes</qex> and novices.</q>
<rj><qau>Bp. Hall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Puisny</ent>⟦br⟧
